                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18331017-52-victim582 t18331017-52-viclabel296"></join>. On the 5th of October, I was a little drunk - I was in <placeName id="t18331017-52-crimeloc297">Shoreditch</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18331017-52-crimeloc297" type="placeName" value="Shoreditch"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18331017-52-crimeloc297" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18331017-52-off294 t18331017-52-crimeloc297"></join> about half-past ten o'clock at night, and had two pairs of trousers under my arm; I saw the prisoner, he asked me where I was going - I had not known him before; I said I was going to Shoreditch; he then snatched my trousers from me - one pair I had bought new, and the other had been repaired; he then said, "This is your way;" I said, "I have lost my trousers;" he gave me back one pair, and said, "Here are your trousers;" I said, "I have lost another pair;" he said, "I have not got them, and know nothing about them;" the policeman then came up, and I told him I had lost a pair of trousers, and I supposed this man had got them; the officer took him round the corner, and I saw this pair drop from him - I gave him into custody.</p>
               <p>
            
