             (police constable C 170). I took the prisoner, and saw him drop these trousers.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I saw him getting up from a step of a door; he dropped one pair of trousers, and I gave them to him; he then asked if there was not another pair of black ones; I said, "I don't see them;" he then spoke to the policeman, and went down the street with him - they then came back, and the policeman took hold of me and searched to see if I had them, but I had not - he took me a short distance, and then he dropped this pair at my feet.</p>
